## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="3505d-115"><xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule.%23ctor%2A>コンス トラクターの初期化、<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule.Id%2A>プロパティ。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="3505d-115">The <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule.%23ctor%2A> constructor initializes the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule.Id%2A> property.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="3505d-116">識別子は、指定された文法内で一意である必要があります。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="3505d-116">The identifier must be unique within a given grammar.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="3505d-117"><xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule.%23ctor%2A>コンス トラクターがスローされます、<xref:System.FormatException>次の状況で。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="3505d-117">The <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule.%23ctor%2A> constructor throws a <xref:System.FormatException> in the following circumstances:</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="3505d-118">`id` 定義されている有効な XML 名でない[Extensible Markup Language (XML) 1.0 (Fifth Edition)](https://www.w3.org/TR/REC-xml/)します。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="3505d-118">`id` is not a valid XML name, as defined in [Extensible Markup Language (XML) 1.0 (Fifth Edition)](https://www.w3.org/TR/REC-xml/).</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="3505d-119">この定義を再検討するには、有効な XML 名は、文字、アンダー スコア ('_')、またはコロンで始める必要があります (': ') と (もは XML 仕様で定義された) 0 個以上の NameChar 文字の後に指定できます。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="3505d-119">To paraphrase this definition, a valid XML name must begin with a letter, an underscore ('_'), or a colon (':') and can be followed by zero or more NameChar characters (also defined in the XML specification).</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="3505d-120">`id` "NULL"または"VOID"または「不要な」です。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="3505d-120">`id` is "NULL" or "VOID" or "GARBAGE".</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="3505d-121">`id` 無効なルール ID の少なくとも 1 つの文字が含まれています。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="3505d-121">`id` contains at least one invalid rule ID character.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="3505d-122">これらの文字は: '?'、' \*'、'+'、'&#124;'、' (',')、' ^'、'$'、'/'、';'、'.'、'='、'\<'、' >'、' ['、']'、' {'、'} '、'\\\\'、' '、'\t'、'\r' および '\n'。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="3505d-122">These characters are: '?', '\*', '+', '&#124;', '(', '), '^', '$', '/', ';', '.', '=', '\<', '>', '[', ']', '{', '}', '\\\\', ' ', '\t', '\r', and '\n'.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="3505d-123">次の例は、フレーズを認識する文法を作成後に「は、ワールド カップを勝ち抜いて民族」ワールド カップが勝利した国の名前。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="3505d-123">The following example creates a grammar that recognizes the phrase "A nation that has won the World Cup is" followed by the name of a country that has won the World Cup.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="3505d-124">例は、作成、<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule>という名前のオブジェクト`winnerRule`識別子で合格と`WorldCupWinner`として、<xref:System.String>します。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="3505d-124">The example creates a <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule> object named `winnerRule` and passes in the identifier  `WorldCupWinner` as a <xref:System.String>.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="3505d-125"><xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf>の配列の新しいオブジェクトには<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsItem>ルールによって認識される代替手段を含むオブジェクト。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="3505d-125">The <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf> object consists of an array of new <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsItem> objects containing alternatives to be recognized by the rule.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
public void WorldSoccerWinners ()  
{  
  
  // Create an SrgsDocument, create a new rule  
  // and set its scope to public.  
  SrgsDocument document = new SrgsDocument();  
  SrgsRule winnerRule = new SrgsRule("WorldCupWinner");  
  winnerRule.Scope = SrgsRuleScope.Public;  
  
  // Add the introduction.  
  winnerRule.Elements.Add(new SrgsItem("A nation that has won the world cup is: "));  
  
  // Create the rule for the European nations.  
  SrgsOneOf oneOfEurope = new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {new SrgsItem("England"),   
    new SrgsItem("France"), new SrgsItem("Germany"), new SrgsItem("Italy")});  
  SrgsRule ruleEurope = (new SrgsRule("EuropeanNations", new SrgsElement[] {oneOfEurope}));  
  
  // Create the rule for the South American nations.  
  SrgsOneOf oneOfSAmerica = new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {new SrgsItem("Argentina"),   
    new SrgsItem("Brazil"), new SrgsItem("Uruguay")});  
  SrgsRule ruleSAmerica = (new SrgsRule("SouthAmericanNations", new SrgsElement[] {oneOfSAmerica}));  
  
  // Add references to winnerRule for ruleEurope and ruleSAmerica.  
  winnerRule.Elements.Add(new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {(new SrgsItem   
    (new SrgsRuleRef(ruleEurope))), new SrgsItem(new SrgsRuleRef(ruleSAmerica))}));  
  
  // Add all the rules to the document and make winnerRule   
  // the root rule of the document.  
  document.Rules.Add(new SrgsRule[] {winnerRule, ruleEurope, ruleSAmerica});  
  document.Root = winnerRule;  
}  
```

  
  
